Beschreibung Wenn der Autor ein Softwaresystem ist, dann ist die Angabe des functionCode NICHT ERLAUBT (Regel: CH-MSET-HAUT2)

Description The CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry code must be 55607006 (SNOMED CT - Problem).
Beschreibung Der CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry code muss 55607006 (SNOMED CT - Problem) sein.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00024 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or @negationInd='false'
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, the value of negationInd must be set to false.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry muss der Wert von negationInd false sein
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00025 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or cda:text[@nullFlavor='NA']
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, a text entry is not permitted, so the 'text' element shall have a nullFlavor with value 'NA'.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, ist das text entry nicht erlaubt. Das 'text' Element muss mit nullFlavor NA angegeben werden.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00026 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: WarningWarnungAlerteAllarme
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or cda:author
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, an author entry shall be specified if known.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry soll ein author entry angegeben werden, wenn bekannt.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00027 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(cda:author) or (cda:author/cda:time/@value and cda:author/cda:assignedAuthor/cda:id[@extension and @root='1.3.88'])
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, if the 'author' element is present, then the time of creation shall be recorded in the 'time' element and the GLN of the data enterer must be declared in the 'id' element of 'assignedAuthor'.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry muss das Datum der Eintragung im time Element beim author angegeben werden. Ebenfalls muss die GLN der eintragenden Person im 'id' element von 'assignedAuthor' deklariert werden.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00028 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or (not(cda:value) or (cda:value[@nullFlavor] or cda:author))
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, the 'author' element is required when a value is given (Rule CH-MSET-AUTH1).
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry muss ein 'author' Element angegeben werden wenn ein 'value' vorhanden ist (Regel CH-MSET-AUTH1).
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00029 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or (cda:effectiveTime/cda:low[@nullFlavor='UNK'] and cda:effectiveTime/cda:high[@nullFlavor='UNK'])
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, the effectiveTime must have the 'low' and 'high' elements containing a nullFlavor with value 'UNK'.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, muss die effectiveTime das 'low' und 'high' element mit nullFlavor 'UNK' aufweisen.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00030 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or (cda:value[@xsi:type='CD' and (@nullFlavor or (@codeSystem='2.16.756.5.30.1.127.3.1.20080401.1' and @code=$vvk-edi-codeSystem[@root='2.16.756.5.30.1.127.3.1.20080401.1']/code/@value))])
Description In CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, the code in the 'value' element must contain a valid code from the value set 'diseaseName (ICR-DHA, chapter 2.1.1); OID: 2.16.756.5.30.1.127.3.1.20080401.1'.
Beschreibung Im CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, muss der code im 'value' Element einen gültigen Code aus dem Value-Set 'diseaseName (VVK-EDI, Kapitel 2.1.1); OID: 2.16.756.5.30.1.127.3.1.20080401.1' enthalten.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00031 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: InformationInformationInformationInformazioni
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(ancestor::cda:section/cda:code[@code='11450-4']) or cda:entryRelationship[@typeCode='SUBJ' and @inversionInd='true']/cda:act/cda:templateId[@root='1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.2']
Description The CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry does not contain an annotation comment (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.2).
Beschreibung Das CDA-CH-MSET Problem Entry, enthält keinen Kommentar (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.2).

Description The following rules describe the tests on the CDA-CH Medication Section Templates
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_cda-ch_medication-section-0101_as00131 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore

Description CDA-CH 'External Reference' must contain a <text> element that contains the Base64 encoded document and a <reference> element pointing to the narrative text where the reference is recorded. Alternatively the external document may be referenced by URL. In this case the same URL MUST be declared using the <linkHTML> element in the narrative text.

Rule ID:Regel ID:ID de la règle:ID de la regola: cda-ch-mset_ru00093 Pattern:Pattern:Motif:[Pattern@it]: cda-ch-mset_1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.2-errors_pa00089
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00336 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:templateId[@root = "1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.2), the Problem Concern Entry has a template identifier of 1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.2, and is a subtype of the Concern Entry, and so must also conform to that specification, with the template identifier of 1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1. These elements are required and shall be recorded exactly as indicated.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00337 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: (cda:entryRelationship[@typeCode = "SUBJ"] and cda:entryRelationship/*/cda:templateId[@root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5"] and cda:entryRelationship[@inversionInd="false"]) or (cda:subjectOf[@typeCode = "SUBJ"] and cda:subjectOf/*/cda:templateId[@root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5"] and cda:subjectOf[@inversionInd="false"])
Description In IHE PCC Problem Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.2), the Problem Concern Entry shall contain one or more problem entries that conform to the Problem Entry template 1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5. For CDA this SHALL be represented with the <entryRelationship> element. For HL7 Version 3 Messages, this SHALL be represented as a <subjectOf> element. The typeCode SHALL be SUBJ and inversionInd SHALL be false.

Rule ID:Regel ID:ID de la règle:ID de la regola: cda-ch-mset_ru00094 Pattern:Pattern:Motif:[Pattern@it]: cda-ch-mset_1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1-errors_pa00090

Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: ../cda:act
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the Concern Entry can only be used on acts.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00339 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: ../cda:act[@classCode="ACT"] and ../cda:act[@moodCode="EVN"]
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), all concerns reflect the act of recording (<act classCode='ACT'>) the event (moodCode='EVN') of being concerned about a problem, allergy or other issue about the patient condition.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00340 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:templateId[@root="2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.1.27"]
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the required template identifiers indicates this Concern Entry conforms to the Concern Content module. This content module inherits constraints from the HL7 CCD Template for problem acts, and so also includes that template identifier (2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.1.27).
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00341 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:id
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the Concern Entry requires id element.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00342 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:code[@nullFlavor="NA"]
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the code is not applicable to a concern act (Concern Entry), and so shall be recorded as <code nullFlavor='NA'/>.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00343 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:statusCode[@code="active" or @code="suspended" or @code="aborted" or @code="completed"]
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the statusCode associated with any concern must be one of the following values: active, suspended, aborted or completed.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00344 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:effectiveTime/cda:low
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the <effectiveTime> element records the starting and ending times during which the concern (Concern Entry) was active. The <low> element shall be present.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00345 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: (cda:statusCode[@code="completed" or @code="aborted"] and cda:effectiveTime/cda:high) or (cda:statusCode[@code="active" or @code="suspended"] and not(cda:effectiveTime/cda:high))
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), the <effectiveTime> element records the starting and ending times during the concern (Concern Entry). The <high> element shall be present for concerns in the completed or aborted state, and shall not be present otherwise.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00346 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: (cda:entryRelationship[@typeCode="SUBJ"] and cda:entryRelationship/*/cda:templateId[@root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5" or @root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.6"]) or (cda:sourceOf[@typeCode="SUBJ" and @inversionInd="false"] and cda:sourceOf/*/cda:templateId[@root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5" or @root="1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.6"])
Description In IHE PCC Concern Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5.1), each concern (Concern Entry) is about one or more related problems or allergies. This entry shall contain one or more problem or allergy entries that conform to the specification in section Problem Entry or Allergies and Intolerances. This is how a series of related observations can be grouped as a single concern. For CDA this SHALL be represented with the <entryRelationship> element. For HL7 Version 3 Messages, this SHALL be represented as a <sourceOf> element. The typeCode SHALL be SUBJ for both HL7 Version 3 and CDA. HL7 Version 3 additionally requires that inversionInd SHALL be false.

Rule ID:Regel ID:ID de la règle:ID de la regola: cda-ch-mset_ru00095 Pattern:Pattern:Motif:[Pattern@it]: cda-ch-mset_1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5-errors_pa00091
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00347 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: self::cda:observation[@classCode="OBS" and @moodCode="EVN"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), the basic pattern for reporting a problem uses the CDA <observation> element, setting the classCode='OBS' to represent that this is an observation of a problem, and the moodCode='EVN', to represent that this is an observation that has in fact taken place.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00348 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:templateId[@root="2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.1.28"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), <templateId> elements identify this under both IHE and CCD specifications (2.16.840.1.113883.10.20.1.28). This CCD template ID SHALL be included.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00349 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:id
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), the specific Problem Entry observation being recorded must have an identifier (<id>) that shall be provided for tracking purposes. If the source EMR does not or cannot supply an intrinsic identifier, then a GUID shall be provided as the root, with no extension (e.g., <id root='CE1215CD-69EC-4C7B-805F-569233C5E159'/>). At least one identifier must be present, more than one may appear.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00350 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:text
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), the <text> element is required and points to the text describing the problem being recorded; including any dates, comments, et cetera. The <reference> contains a URI in value attribute. This URI points to the free text description of the problem in the document that is being described.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00351 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:statusCode[@code="completed"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), a clinical document normally records only those condition observation events that have been completed, not observations that are in any other state. Therefore, the <statusCode> shall always have code='completed' for Problem Entry.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00352 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:effectiveTime/cda:low[@value or @nullFlavor = "UNK"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), the effectiveTime <low> value should normally be present in Problem Entry. There are exceptions, such as for the case where the patient may be able to report that they had chicken pox, but are unsure when. In this case, the <effectiveTime> element shall have a <low> element with a nullFlavor attribute set to 'UNK'.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00353 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:value[@xsi:type="CD"]
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), the <value> is the condition that was found. This element is required. While the value of Problem Entry code may be a coded or an un-coded string, the type is always a coded value (xsi:type='CD').
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00354 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: (cda:value[@code and @codeSystem]) or (not(cda:value[@code]) and not(cda:value[@codeSystem]))
Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), if Problem Entry value is coded, the code and codeSystem attributes shall be present. If uncoded, all attributes other than xsi:type='CD' must be absent.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00355 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore

Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), only one optional severity entry relationship is allowed.

The typeCode SHALL be SUBJ and inversionInd SHALL be true. For CDA this SHALL be represented with the <entryRelationship> element.

Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00359 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: ErrorFehlerErreurErrore

Description In IHE PCC Problem Entry (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.5), an optional <entryRelationship> element may be present in Problem Entry indicating the clinical status of the problem, e.g., resolved, in remission, active. The typeCode SHALL be REFR and inversionInd SHALL be false. For CDA this SHALL be represented with the <entryRelationship> element.

Rule ID:Regel ID:ID de la règle:ID de la regola: cda-ch-mset_ru00114 Pattern:Pattern:Motif:[Pattern@it]: cda-ch-mset_1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.12-warnings_pa00109

Description In IHE PCC Immunizations (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.12), in a CDA document, the URI given in the value attribute of the <reference> element points to an element in the narrative content that contains the complete text describing the immunization activity. Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00429 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: WarningWarnungAlerteAllarme
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(cda:effectiveTime/@value) or (string-length(cda:effectiveTime/@value) >= 8)
Description In IHE PCC Immunizations (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.12), the effectiveTime element shall be present and should contain a time value that indicates the date of the substance administration. If the date is unkown, this shall be recorded using the nullFlavor attribute, with the reason that the information is unknown being specified. Otherwise, the date shall be recorded, and should have precision of at least the day.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00430 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: WarningWarnungAlerteAllarme
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: not(cda:routeCode[@code]) or cda:routeCode[@displayName]
Description In IHE PCC Immunizations (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.12), the <routeCode> element specifies the route of administration using the HL7 RouteOfAdministration vocabulary. A code must be specified if the route is known, and the displayName attribute should be specified.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00431 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: WarningWarnungAlerteAllarme
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:approachSiteCode/cda:originalText/cda:reference
Description In IHE PCC Immunizations (1.3.6.1.4.1.19376.1.5.3.1.4.12), the <approachSiteCode> element describes the site of medication administrion. It may be coded to a controlled vocabulary that lists such sites (e.g., SNOMED-CT). In CDA documents, this element contains a URI in the value attribute of the <reference> that points to the text in the narrative identifying the site. In a message, the <originalText> element shall contain the text identifying the site.
Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID:Assert ID: cda-ch-mset_as00432 Role:Kategorie:Catégorie:Categoria: WarningWarnungAlerteAllarme
Assert:Assert:Assert:Assert: cda:doseQuantity
Description In Immunizations, the dose is specified in the <doseQuantity> element. If a dose range is given (e.g., 1-2 tablets, or 325-750mg), then the <low> and <high> bounds are specified in their respective elements, otherwise both <low> and <high> have the same value. If the dose is in countable units (tablets, caplets, "eaches"), then the unit attribute is not sent. Otherwise the units are sent. The unit attribute should be derived from the HL7 UnitsOfMeasureCaseSensitive vocabulary.
